cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.RO, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with removing undesired objects from RGB-D sequences and inpainting techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves 3D reconstruction, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics). The use of Markov random field (MRF) based approach suggests the involvement of machine learning, which is covered under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves image warping, which is a common technique in robotics and autonomous systems, hence it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the use of multi-view inpainting suggests the involvement of multimedia, which is covered under cs.MM (Multimedia).
